description: Absorb a block as a brush into your brush inventory
absorb.name: Absorb

description: Add a spell to a player or wand
add_spell.name: Add Spell

description: Force a mob to focus on the caster
aggro.name: Aggro

description: Increase an entity's air supply
air_supply.name: Air Supply

description: Target all entities in the current world, or optionally in all worlds
all_entities.name: All Entities

description: Experimental incomplete action, do not use.
animate.name: Animate

description: Apply or clear cooldowns on one or more of a player's spells
apply_cooldown.name: Apply Cooldown

description: Target all entities within a radius
area_of_effect.name: Area Of Effect

description: Create an area of effect cloud entity. Shortcut for the SpawnEntity action.
area_of_effect_cloud.name: Area Of Effect Cloud

description: Create a projectile that uses an armor stand.
This can be used with invisible armor stands holding items from a custom resource pack for detailed custom 3D projectiles.
armor_stand_projectile.name: Armor Stand Projectile

description: Move up through blocks above the player
ascend.name: Ascend

description: Performs its sub-actions outside of the flow of the rest of the action list
This can be used to launch several projectiles without waiting for them to hit, for instance.
asynchronous.name: Asynchronous

description: Looks in a specific direction for blocks matching the destructible list
block_search.name: Block Search

description: Breaks a block naturally
Can be configured to only break blocks below a certain vanilla durability
Applies packet-based block breaking effects before fully destroying a block
If the player does not have break permission, the visual breaking effects will still be applied but the block will not fully break
break_block.name: Break Block

description: Change the brush used for contained actions
Capable of choosing a random brush from a 'brushes' proability map
brush.name: Brush

description: Open the brush selector GUI
brush_select.name: Brush Select

description: Light the target block on fire
burn.name: Burn

description: Cancel any active spells, or specific spells, for the target player
cancel.name: Cancel

description: Remove the target entity and replace it with a spawn egg that will respawn the entity
capture.name: Capture

description: Change the biome of the target block
change_biome.name: Change Biome

description: A complicated compound action that can be used to run sub-actions using a modified context
The action context includes things such as the source and target locations and entities
change_context.name: Change Context

description: Change the parameters of a spell mid-cast
change_parameters.name: Change Parameters

description: Move a player to another server
Requires a BungeCord server network
change_server.name: Change Server

description: Move the player to a different world, but with the same coordinate as in their current world
Can be configured with a set of worlds and scales, for instance to mimic nether:overworld 1:8 scale
change_world.name: Change World

description: Test if a block is in the destructible list
Only runs its sub-actions if the block passes the destructible check.
check_block.name: Check Block

description: Test if an entity is allowed to target
Only runs its sub-actions if the entity passes the checks.
check_entity.name: Check Entity

description: Test if a player has or does not have an amount of mana
Only runs its sub-actions if player's mana is as required.
check_mana.name: Check Mana

description: Run one or more commands

Support the following variables: @spell, @pd (caster display name), @p, @pn (same as @p, caster name), @uuid, @world, @x, @y, @z, @tworld, @tx, @ty, @tz (target location), @td (target display name), @t, @tn (same as @t, target name), @tuuid
command.name: Command

description: Target all entities within a cone in front of the caster
cone_of_effect.name: Cone Of Effect

description: Count up the number of blocks or entities targeted and message the count to the caster
count.name: Count

description: Target the first solid block below the current target
cover.name: Cover

description: Create a PreciousStones field
create_field.name: Create Field

description: Create a Towny plot
create_plot.name: Create Plot

description: A flexible custom projectile
This projectile can be made to reflect off surfaces, hit multiple entities or blocks, run spell actions as it travels, and more.
It is able to mimic a gravity-bound projectile, home in on a target, and perform staged animations
This is the base class for AmorStandProjectile and EntityProjectile
custom_projectile.name: Custom Projectile

description: Change blocks to other blocks using a mapping list
cycle_block.name: Cycle Block

description: Change entities to other entity types using a mapping list
cycle_entity.name: Cycle Entity

description: Target all blocks in a cylinder
cylinder.name: Cylinder

description: Damage the target entity
damage.name: Damage

description: Deactivate active spells for the target
deactivate.name: Deactivate

description: Turn on the spell debugger
debugger.name: Debugger

description: Don't proceed to the next action until some amount of time has passed
Can be used at the beginning of a spell for a 'warmup' period, and will advertise the warmup in spell lore if the warmup parameter is used.
delay.name: Delay

description: Move down through the blocks underneath the caster
descend.name: Descend

description: Temporarily disable block physics updates
disable_physics.name: Disable Physics

description: Remove the item the target is holding
For target players will optionally move the item into their inventory instead of throwing it on the ground.
disarm.name: Disarm

description: Target all blocks within a 2D circular disc
disc.name: Disc

description: Apply a disguise to an entity
Requires the ProtocolLib and LibsDisguises plugins
disguise.name: Disguise

description: Open or close a door
door.name: Door

description: Destroy blocks and drop items as if they were broken naturally
drop.name: Drop

description: Drop an item on the ground
drop_item.name: Drop Item

description: Cause a target creeper to be electrified
electrify.name: Electrify

description: Randomly upgrade a wand, as if enchanted via the old enchanting system
Will add spells and other properties to a wand randomly, as determined by its current path configuration
enchant_wand.name: Enchant Wand

description: A CustonmProjectile with an entity attached
Ever want to attack someone using a flying llama?
entity_projectile.name: Entity Projectile

description: Show a GUI allowing the player to select nearby entities to target
Will run its sub-actions with the selected entity as the target
entity_select.name: Entity Select

description: Create a vanilla explosion
Due to the exponential fall-off used by vanilla Minecraft for calculating explosion damage to entities, use of this action is discouraged.
Explosions can be easily gamed by wise players in PvP situations once they learn the exact distance to cast from to get the center on top of the target entity.
explosion.name: Explosion

description: Apply protection from falling to a target entity for a period of time.
fall_protection.name: Fall Protection

description: Fill the target's hunger bars
feed.name: Feed

description: Fills a wand with all available spells
fill_wand.name: Fill Wand

description: Launch a vanilla firework
Can work like a projectile, running actions when the firework explodes.
firework.name: Firework

description: Grow flowers
Can randomly select flowers from a probability map
flower.name: Flower

description: Freeze a block
Turns air blocks into snow, increases height of snow blocks, turns water into ice and lava into stone, and puts out fires.
freeze.name: Freeze

description: Give an item directly to a player
give_item.name: Give Item

description: Force a player to glide
Does not necessarily require that the player is wearing an elytra
glide.name: Glide

description: Turn baby entities into adults, zombies into giants, and optionally skeletons into wither skeletons
grow_entity.name: Grow Entity

description: Restore an entity's health.
Can restore a specific amount of health, or a percentage of max health
heal.name: Heal

description: Light an entity on fire, or put out a fire
ignite.name: Ignite

description: Show a player a specific inventory
Can be used to view the player's ender chest, show them a disposable chest inventory, or the inventory of the target container
inventory.name: Inventory

description: Close the target player's inventory
inventory_close.name: Inventory Close

description: Create a GUI shop that can sell vanilla or magic items
The shop is also capable of casting spells on players
item_shop.name: Item Shop

description: Kill the target entity
Deals 100 x the entity's max health in damage, just to be safe.
kill.name: Kill

description: Modify the light level of the target block
Requires the LightAPI plugin
Do to issues with LightAPI, lighting changes do not reliably undo!
light.name: Light

description: Strike lighting at the target
Can spawn a fully active lightning bolt, or just the visual effect
lightning.name: Lightning

description: Target all blocks along a single line
line.name: Line

description: Apply a vanilla lock to a container
Will give the caster a key item they may use to unlock the container
The key and lock will use the caster's UUID, the item name is obfuscated with the enchantment text decoration
Can also be used to unlock a container
lock.name: Lock

description: Send a chat, action bar or title message to the target player or caster
message.name: Message

description: Modify a block by changing its type
Can also be used to spawn falling blocks in the place of a block that was removed
Falling blocks can be given velocity for explosion type block effects
modify_block.name: Modify Block

description: Tag a block as breakable so that other spells can break the block
modify_breakable.name: Modify Breakable

description: Change the player's game mode
modify_game_mode.name: Modify Game Mode

description: Add or remove mana from a player or wand
modify_mana.name: Modify Mana

description: Modify the properties of a player or wand
modify_properties.name: Modify Properties

description: Change a block so that it will reflect spells
modify_reflective.name: Modify Reflective

description: Add or remove Spell Points
modify_s_p.name: Modify SP

description: Modify the walk speed attribute of the target
modify_walk_speed.name: Modify Walk Speed

description: Force the caster to mount the target entity
mount.name: Mount

description: Mount an armor stand, optionally creating and removing the armor stand
This is the action that powers broomsticks and other vehicles
Using custom resource pack models, this can be used to implement driveable cars, planes or just about anything by applying velocity to the armor stand when mounted
It has many parameters for handling crashing, hovering, and other options
mount_armor_stand.name: Mount Armor Stand

description: Move a block from one location to another
move_block.name: Move Block

description: Repeat a set of actions mulitple times in parallel
Will fall back to using the 'repeat' parameter if 'multiply' is not specified
multiply.name: Multiply

description: Force the target entity to face a specific direction
orient.name: Orient

description: Runs each action in the list of sub-actions in parallel, rather than sequentially
parallel.name: Parallel

description: Target all blocks in a 2D plane
plane.name: Plane

description: Play a specific set of effects from the spell's effects list
play_effects.name: Play Effects

description: Play music from a vanilla record disc to the target player
play_record.name: Play Record

description: Play a sound to the target player
Can be used with vanilla sounds or custom sounds from a resource pack
play_sound.name: Play Sound

description: Show the caster a GUI with heads for all players on the server, allowing them to choose a player who will be the target of the sub-action list
player_select.name: Player Select

description: Apply or remove vanilla potion effects from the target
potion_effect.name: Potion Effect

description: Change the state of redstone blocks such as levers and buttons
power_block.name: Power Block

description: Execute or skip sub-actions based on a random chance
probability.name: Probability

description: Launch a vanilla projectile
projectile.name: Projectile

description: Randomly choose one from the set of sub-actions to execute
random.name: Random

description: Show a customizeable GUI of warps and other locations
Can be used with warps created by Essentials or CommandBook
recall.name: Recall

description: Recursively follows blocks that match the spell's destructible list
Can be configured to only follow a specific list of block faces, such as only filling downward
recurse.name: Recurse

description: Remove an entity from the world completely, without killing it or having it drop loot
remove_entity.name: Remove Entity

description: Repair the target item, or items in the target player's inventory
repair_item.name: Repair Item

description: Repeat sub-actions a number of times in sequence
repeat.name: Repeat

description: Performs targeting as normal, passing the new target to its sub-actions
retarget.name: Retarget

description: Mount and control the target entity
This is the base action for MountArmorStand
ride_entity.name: Ride Entity

description: Target all blocks in a ring
ring.name: Ring

description: Show the caster a customizeable GUI
This gui can be used to sell items, or cast spells
This is similar to ItemShop but more customizeable, allowing for requirements for each item, different costs or a mix of items and spells.
selector.name: Selector

description: Group a set of actions together and run them in serial
This is mainly useful inside of actions like Random or Parallel, to group a set of actions together as a single option for the parent action.
serial.name: Serial

description: Remove a block and replace it with a skull item representation of the block
Only works on a very limited set of blocks, the ones for which Mojang has provided MHF skins.
shrink_block.name: Shrink Block

description: Change entities to baby entities
can apply damage to entities and drop skulls for them when killed
shrink_entity.name: Shrink Entity

description: This action is not complete, do not use. It is intended to replace SimulateSpell
Runs a simulation of Conway's game of life
The simulation can have custom rules, and can be run in 2D or 3D
simulate.name: Simulate

description: Show the skill selection GUI to the caster
This is the same GUI that a player would get if using the /mskills command
skill_selector.name: Skill Selector

description: Runs its sub actions every N iterations, skipping them the rest of the time
This is most often used to slow down a spell in chunks, by skipping a Delay sub-action
This can be used for block animations to allow ModifyBlock to run N times per tick with a delay in between
skip.name: Skip

description: Spawn a new entity in the world
Can be used with a magic mob, a full custom mob config, a simple vanilla mob or a random probability table of mobs
spawn_entity.name: Spawn Entity

description: Show the caster the spell progress GUI, which will show them spells they have that are upgradeable, and the requirements to upgrade them.
spell_progress.name: Spell Progress

description: A spell-specific variant of ItemShop
Can be used to spell a specific set of spells, cast spells on the buyer, or automatically show players the spells available to them at their current path.
This is the main method of progression for players that is available via the enchantment table GUI
spell_shop.name: Spell Shop

description: Target all blocks in a sphere
sphere.name: Sphere

description: Randomly modify the target location or source direction
spread.name: Spread

description: Temporarily remove the player's wand and return it on undo
stash_wand.name: Stash Wand

description: Stop running the spell and finish it immediately
stop.name: Stop

description: Apply super protection to a player, as if they were holding a wand with the 'protected' property
A super protected player can't be damaged in any way or targeted by any spells
super_protection.name: Super Protection

description: Spawn a primed TNT entity
Can run a set of actions when the TNT detonates
t_n_t.name: TNT

description: Remove items from the player's inventory
take_item.name: Take Item

description: Tame the target entity and set its owner as the caster
tame.name: Tame

description: Teleport the caster to the target location
teleport.name: Teleport

description: Throw a falling block entity
Can run a set of actions when the block lands
throw_block.name: Throw Block

description: Throw an item
Can run a set of actions when the item despawns
throw_item.name: Throw Item

description: Target all loaded tile entities
tile_entities.name: Tile Entities

description: Change the time of the target world
Can also change the phase of the moon
time.name: Time

description: Attach a torch to the target block
torch.name: Torch

description: Grow a tree at the target location
This uses the vanilla tree generation algorithm and is not undoable
Can be made to choose the type of tree based on the biome of the target block
tree.name: Tree

description: Undoes spells
Can undo the last spell cast by the caster, the last spell cast by the target, or the last spell to have affected the target block.
May require that the spell was cast recently or was cast by the caster of the undoing spell.
Can also be used to undo changes performed in the current spell, including only undoing a limit set of changes in FIFO order. This can be used to create complex animations within a single spell.
undo.name: Undo

description: Vanish the target player, making them completely invisible to other players
vanish.name: Vanish

description: Apply velocity to the target entity
Can be used to push or pull the entity away or towards the caster
Can modify the velicity applied based on the target's distance from the ground, for a spell that applies a higher speed when up in the air
velocity.name: Velocity

description: Target all blocks within a cuboid volume
volume.name: Volume

description: Force the target to wear a specific block or item on their head
Can also be used to force the caster to wear the target block
wear.name: Wear

description: Change the weather in the target world
weather.name: Weather

description: Actions that contain other actions
compound.name: Compound

description: Actions that modify the structor or process of a spell
control.name: Control

description: Actions that effect entities
entity.name: Entity

description: Properties of magic mobs
mob.name: Mob

description: Actions that effect only players
player.name: Player

description: Wand properties
wand.name: Wand

description: An animated swirl that follows the shape of a sphere
animated_ball.name: Animated Ball

description: An arc that extends from the source location to the target location
arc.name: Arc

description: A model of an atom with a nuclues and one or more orbitals
atom.name: Atom

description: A big explosion with loud sounds
big_bang.name: Big Bang

description: Make it look like a player is bleeding, an optionally apply the hurt effect
bleed.name: Bleed

description: A 2D circle
circle.name: Circle

description: A puffy cloud
cloud.name: Cloud

description: Draw an image or animated gif using redstone or other colored particles
colored_image.name: Colored Image

description: A swirly cone extending out from the source location
cone.name: Cone

description: A wireframe cube
cube.name: Cube

description: A cylinder that may be hollow or solid
cylinder.name: Cylinder

description: A shiny disco ball in the sky
disco_ball.name: Disco Ball

description: Extends a strand of DNA with helixes rotating around a base
dna.name: Dna

description: A torus shape
donut.name: Donut

description: Strands of fire that shoot out in arcs
dragon.name: Dragon

description: A sphere that resembles the earth
earth.name: Earth

description: Uses equations to render a particle each tick.
Is capable of parametric equations, rendering multiple particles per tick.
Equations use a 't' variable by default to represent the current tick, this variable starts at zero and counts up.
equation.name: Equation

description: A large explosion
explode.name: Explode

description: Make something look like it's on fire
flame.name: Flame

description: A fountain of particles shooting up in the sky
fountain.name: Fountain

description: Create a 2D wireframe grid
grid.name: Grid

description: Creates a 2D heart in 3D space
heart.name: Heart

description: A flat spiralling helix
helix.name: Helix

description: Waving hills
hill.name: Hill

description: A single particle appears above the target
icon.name: Icon

description: Render a monochrome image from an image file or animated gif.
Black pixels will be skipped, all other pixels display as the selected particle type
image.name: Image

description: Apply velocity to the target entity
jump.name: Jump

description: Extend a line from the source to the target
line.name: Line

description: Make hearts bubble out of the target
love.name: Love

description: Modify any other effect using equations
Equations can be applied to any parameter of the contained effect.
Equations can also be used to move the entire effect around.
modified.name: Modified

description: A ring of musical notes
music.name: Music

description: Create a simple graph of an equation using separate x and y equations.
This is primarily intended for testing equations, and not really meant to be used for in-game effects
plot.name: Plot

description: Creat a dome around the target
shield.name: Shield

description: Send the target entity flying into the sky
sky_rocket.name: Sky Rocket

description: Make it appear as though the target is smoldering
smoke.name: Smoke

description: Create a 3D sphere
sphere.name: Sphere

description: Create a 2D star
star.name: Star

description: Render text in the air using particles
text.name: Text

description: A swirling tornado of particles
tornado.name: Tornado

description: Trail particles behind the target entity
trace.name: Trace

description: Make the target entity change directions
turn.name: Turn

description: Create a swirling vortex
vortex.name: Vortex

description: Rings that descend around the target, as if they had stepped on a teleporter pad
warp.name: Warp

description: Create a wavy horizontal plane
wave.name: Wave

description: A map of events to actions to run. The most comment event used by all spells is 'cast'
Actions determine the behavior of a spell, defining what it does
actions.name: Actions

description: The currently active brush, used with engineering magic
active_brush.name: Active Brush

description: A list of costs to be deducted every second this spell is active
active_costs.name: Active Costs

description: The currently active spell for this wand, which will be cast when performing a bound cast action
active_spell.name: Active Spell

description: A map of potion effects to add to the target
add_effects.name: Add Effects

description: Whether or not this mob has 'AI'. A mob with AI turned off will not move or react, and also can not be pushed by velocity.
ai.name: AI

description: If set to true, this spell will cast as normal if it misses, meaning it reaches max range without hitting a block or entity
allow_max_range.name: Allow Max Range

description: The spell to cast when performing the action bound to alt_cast on this wand
alternate_spell.name: Alternate Spell

description: The spell to cast when performing the action bound to alt_cast2 on this wand
alternate_spell2.name: Alternate Spell 2

description: Angular velocity of the effect
angular_velocity.name: Angular Velocity

description: Turns the effect by this angle each iteration around the x-axis
angular_velocity_x.name: Angular Velocity X

description: Turns the effect by this angle each iteration around the y-axis
angular_velocity_y.name: Angular Velocity Y

description: Turns the effect by this angle each iteration around the z-axis
angular_velocity_z.name: Angular Velocity Z

description: Whether the purchased item should apply directly to the player's wand
apply_to_wand.name: Apply To Wand

description: Whether or not to apply velocity to spawned falling blocks
apply_velocity.name: Apply Velocity

description: Arcs to build the breath
arcs.name: Arcs

description: Whether this effect should run in a separate thread
Running in a separate thread is better for performance, but can not be used with any effects that do something other than show particle effects
Each effect sets this flag accordingly and generally you should not change it
asynchronous.name: Asynchronous

description: Attributes to apply to the player when holding this wand
If set to passive the attributes will be applied when worn
If set to stack, attributes will add to the player's current attributes
attributes.name: Attributes

description: If set to true, and this effect has a target location, the two locations will orient to face one another
auto_orient.name: Auto Orient

description: The percent change that this spell will backfire, targeting the caster instead of the intended target
backfire_chance.name: Backfire Chance

description: The chance of cancelling a spell when blocking with this wand
block_chance.name: Block Chance

description: A cooldown on blocking spells with this wand
block_cooldown.name: Block Cooldown

description: An angle in radians for blocking
The player must be facing the source of a spell in order to block it
block_fov.name: Block Fov

description: How many blocks this projectile can hit before stopping
Generall the projectile would need to have actions on hit that will remove blocks, otherwise it will continue to hit the same block immediately until it reaches its hit count.
block_hit_count.name: Block Hit Count

description: Apply a global cooldown when using this wand to block a spell
block_mage_cooldown.name: Block Mage Cooldown

description: A percent chance that a spell blocked with this wand will be reflected
block_reflect_chance.name: Block Reflect Chance

description: Set to false to make this wand ignore mana boosts from magic armor
boostable.name: Boostable

description: If set, the wand will bind to a player when they hold it
A bound wand may not be used or taken out of a container by any other player
bound.name: Bound

description: A material or brush to use in this spell
For non-engineering spells this determines the type of block build with actions such as ModifyBlock
Engineering spells generally omit this parameter and use the player's selected brush
brush.name: Brush

description: Where each brush is located in the player's inventory
This is generally only set directly in items or class data, and does not need to be added to a configuration
brush_inventory.name: Brush Inventory

description: How the brushes used for engineering will display in this wand
By default brushes will appear in a separate chest inventory, but brush_mode can be set to 'inventory' to have them mixed in with the spell inventory
brush_mode.name: Brush Mode

description: The engineering brushes this wand can use
brushes.name: Brushes

description: Bypass all build, break and pvp checks.
This is a shortcut for all of the other bypass flags
bypass.name: Bypass

description: This spell will not reflect off of reflective blocks
bypass_backfire.name: Bypass Backfire

description: Allows a spell to break blocks in regions that deny breaking
bypass_break.name: Bypass Break

description: Allows a spell to build blocks in regions that deny building
bypass_build.name: Bypass Build

description: This spell can not be deactivated by other spells
bypass_deactivate.name: Bypass Deactivate

description: This spell can be cast even if the mage has a global cooldown in effect
bypass_mage_cooldown.name: Bypass Mage Cooldown

description: This spell can be cast even if a player would not normally have permission to do so
bypass_permissions.name: Bypass Permissions

description: This spell will bypass friendly fire and super protection restrictions
bypass_protection.name: Bypass Protection

description: This allos a spell to bypass pvp checks, so it can target players in pvp-restricted areas.
bypass_pvp.name: Bypass Pvp

description: Don't take cooldown reduction into affect when applying cooldowns
bypass_reduction.name: Bypass Reduction

description: This spell will not add its changes to the undo queue and cannot be undo
bypass_undo.name: Bypass Undo

description: Whether or not the mob will be allowed to pick up items
can_pickup_items.name: Can Pickup Items

description: Current spells in progress will be cancelled before undoing
cancel.name: Cancel

description: If the spell should cancel any running effects it started when the spell ends
cancel_effects.name: Cancel Effects

description: This spell will be cancelled if the caster casts another spell while this one is in progress
cancel_on_cast_other.name: Cancel On Cast Other

description: This spell will be cancelled if the caster is damaged while this spell is on progress
cancel_on_damage.name: Cancel On Damage

description: Check for permission changes while the spell is running and cancel if the player has no permission
Can be used for brooms, levitate or other lasting effects that should cancel if a player moves into a restricted area
cancel_on_no_permission.name: Cancel On No Permission

description: This spell with cancel if the player lets go of their wand
cancel_on_no_wand.name: Cancel On No Wand

description: If set to false, this spell can not be cancelled by other spells
cancellable.name: Cancellable

description: A probability table of spells to cast
This parameter is deprecated, it is better to use the triggers map
cast.name: Cast

description: How often, in milliseconds, to auto-cast the cast_spell set on this wand
cast_interval.name: Cast Interval

description: Offset the source location for spells cast by this wand
cast_location.name: Cast Location

description: For bow wands, require that the bow be pulled back at least this far before a spell will cast
This is a value from 0 to 1, where 1 is pulled fully back
If not pulled back far enough, the wand will fire a normal arrow, unless the spell inventory is open in which case nothing will fire
cast_min_bowpull.name: Cast Min Bowpull

description: The minimum speed of a player required before the cast_spell on this wand will be cast
This can be used to make a wand or armor with a spell that only activates while a player is moving, or if used with cast_velocity_direction, when a player jumps
cast_min_velocity.name: Cast Min Velocity

description: If set to false, a spell will not consume mana or incur cooldown if it was not successfully cast
cast_on_no_target.name: Cast On No Target

description: Parameters to apply to cast_spell when casting
Does not apply to wands cast via a spell in the normal manner, see overrides for that.
cast_parameters.name: Cast Parameters

description: An item the mob must be holding in order to cast spells
cast_requires_item.name: Cast Requires Item

description: If true, the mob will only cast spells if it has targeted an entity
cast_requires_target.name: Cast Requires Target

description: A spell this wand will cast at regular intervals while held
If set to passive, the wand will only cast if worn as armor
cast_spell.name: Cast Spell

description: Used for wand organization and grouping spells in spell lists and spell books
category.name: Category

description: If set to false, this spell will not check its destructible list at all and can modify any block type
check_destructible.name: Check Destructible

description: The class this wand uses
If set this will be a class-bound wand, meaning it may store some of its properties in a player's class data rather than on the wand item
This can be used to create wands that show spells and mana that a player has, so a player may change wands without losing progress
A player must have access to this class to use the wand, if the class is locked it will need to be unlocked before the player may activate this wand
class.name: Class

description: A set of classes that this wand may attach to
The wand will use the first unlocked class from this list it finds on the player
If the player has none of these classes unlocked they may not activate or use this wand
classes.name: Classes

description: The class this effect or action uses
This determines the type of effect or action that will be performed
code_class.name: Class

description: Can be used to color particles and firework effects
color.name: Color

description: A secondary color for an effect
This is used in firework effects as the secondary color
color2.name: Color2

description: A tertiary color for an effect
color3.name: Color3

description: The color used for particles of the first base of the effect
color_base1.name: Color Base1

description: The color used for particles of the second base of the effect
color_base2.name: Color Base2

description: The color used for the particles in the helix of the effect
color_helix.name: Color Helix

description: The color used for the particles in the nucleus of the effect
color_nucleus.name: Color Nucleus

description: The color used for the particles in the orbital of the effect
color_orbital.name: Color Orbital

description: A field in the effectlib effect to replace with the current cast color, which is generally determined by the casting wand
For example if set to 'color', the 'color' parameter of the contained effectlib effect will be automatically set to the cast color
color_override.name: Color Override

description: Number of columns in the grid
columns.name: Columns

description: The command to execute
command.name: Command

description: Whether this spell can be cast via a command block
command_block_allowed.name: Command Block Allowed

description: A list of commands to execute
commands.name: Commands

description: If changes made by this action should auto-commit, so that they are not undoable
commit.name: Commit

description: Compilation of the heart.
compilaction.name: Compilaction

description: Compresses the heart along the y axis
compress_y_factor_total.name: Compress Y Factor Total

description: A percent reduction used for engineering spells that consume blocks when cast
Currently only the values 1 and 0 are supported, where 1 means the player may use engineering magic without spending blocks
This will appear on the wand lore as 'Manifestation'
consume_reduction.name: Consume Reduction

description: A spell to cast when this wand is consumed
Used for making custom potions or food
consume_spell.name: Consume Spell

description: How long, in milliseconds, a player has to wait before casting this spell again
cooldown.name: Cooldown

description: How long, in milliseconds, a player has to wait before casting this any spells after having cast this one
cooldown_mage.name: Mage Global Cooldown

description: A percent reduction for costs in spells cast by this wand
cost_reduction.name: Cost Reduction

description: The type of costs options in this selector use, if none is specified on the option itself
cost_type.name: Cost Type

description: The costs for casting this spell
costs.name: Costs

description: Set this to scale the amount of damage dealt linearly with the distance to the source
This can be used with an AreaOfEffect to damage targets more the closer they were to the cast target
Set this to the maximum distance, at which the damage amount will drop off to zero
damage_max_distance.name: Damage Max Distance

description: A multiplier to apply to the damage done by this action
This can be used with spell levels or headshot parameters, to make it easy to scale up damage while still being able to tweak the base damage value
damage_multiplier.name: Damage Multiplier

description: Delay to wait before continuing, in milliseconds
delay.name: Delay

description: Delay to wait before starting the effect, in ticks
delay_ticks.name: Delay

description: A description of this wand or spell to show in-game, in the item lore
Can be added directly on the wand or spell config, but it is often better to put all language in the messages.yml file so it can be easily edited and translated.
description.name: Description

description: If true, this spell will disable mana regeneration for the caster while the spell is active
This can be used with toggleable spells that have active costs, to preven the caster's mana regeneration rate from overcoming the cost drain.
disable_mana_regeneration.name: Disable Mana Regeneration

description: Should this effect stop playing if the origin entity becomes invalid?
disappear_with_origin_entity.name: Disappear With Origin Entity

description: Should this effect stop playing if the target entity becomes invalid?
disappear_with_target_entity.name: Disappear With Target Entity

description: Which action the wand should perform when the player uses the drop (Q by default) key
drop.name: Drop Key Binding

description: Set this to scale the amount of block damage done linearly with the distance to the source
This can be used with an AreaOfEffect to damage blocks more the closer they were to the cast target
Set this to the maximum distance, at which the damage amount will drop off to zero
durability_max_distance.name: Durability Max Distance

description: How long an effect or spell should last, in milliseconds
duration.name: Duration

description: A multiplier to apply to the duration of a spell or effect
This can be used with spell levels or headshot parameters, to make it easy to scale up duration while still being able to tweak the base duration
duration_multiplier.name: Duration Multiplier

description: How long, in milliseconds, before this spell can earn its max SP value
Until the cooldown expires the spell will earn no SP, or earn an increasing amount of reduced SP
earns_cooldown.name: Earns Cooldown

description: The maximum amount of SP this spell earns when casting
A spell must be successfully cast to earn SP, this generally means it hit a target that it is allowed to affect
SP earning will scale down after the first cast and slowly ramp back up to max over time, as defined by the earns_cooldown
earns_sp.name: Earns Sp

description: If set, the player will have potion effect bubbles on them while holding this wand
The bubbles will appear in the wand's color
effect_bubbles.name: Effect Bubbles

description: A special color applied to this wand
This color is used in wand particle effects if effect_bubbles is set to true
Many spells also use the wand's color for colored particle effects, via effectlib color_override parameters or single particle spawning.
effect_color.name: Effect Color

description: The key of an effects blocks to play
effect_key.name: Effect

description: A custom particle set on this wand
If effect_particle_interval is set, this partile will spawn in a ring around the player at a fixed interval
Some spell effects may also use this custom particle via the particle_override parameter
effect_particle.name: Effect Particle

description: Number of particles to spawn if effect_particle and effect_particle_interval are set
effect_particle_count.name: Effect Particle Count

description: This can be used to give particles a set speed when spawned
The behavior varies between particle types
This will not work with colored particles
effect_particle_data.name: Effect Particle Data

description: Spawn a ring around the player if effect_particle is set.
This value is in milliseconds
effect_particle_interval.name: Effect Particle Interval

description: The minimum velocity the player must be moving for particle effects to show
effect_particle_min_velocity.name: Effect Particle Min Velocity

description: The vertical offset of particles spawned by this wand, if effect_particle and effect_particle_interval are set
effect_particle_offset.name: Effect Particle Offset

description: The radius of the ring of particles spawned by this wand, if effect_particle and effect_particle_interval are set
effect_particle_radius.name: Effect Particle Radius

description: A sound to play at an interval while holding this wand
effect_sound.name: Effect Sound

description: How often, in milliseconds, to play the effect_sound attached to this wand while a player is holding it
effect_sound_interval.name: Effect Sound Interval

description: The type of effect
effect_type.name: Effect Type

description: An EffectLib effect to play
This must contain at least a 'class' parameter to specify which EffectLib class to display
effectlib.name: Effect Lib Effect

description: Which effects to play
effects.name: Effects

description: If true, the particles produced by these potion effects will be 'ambient', meaning slightly transparent and less noticable
effects_ambient.name: Effects Ambient

description: If false, the potion effects applied will not show as bubble particles
effects_particles.name: Effects Particles

description: This can be used to enable a spell that was disabled via config.yml, or to disable specific default
enabled.name: Enabled

description: The number of times this wand has been enchanted
This is tracked internally and should generally not be used in configurations
enchant_count.name: Enchant Count

description: Enchantments to apply to this item
enchantments.name: Enchantments

description: Vanilla entity attributes to apply to the mob
entity_attributes.name: Entity Attributes

description: The amount of damage to apply to non-player targets
entity_damage.name: Entity Damage

description: A vanilla entity effect, such as HURT
entity_effect.name: Entity Effect

description: Used to control the expected lifespan of the firework, possibly detonating it early
expected_lifespan.name: Expected Lifespan

description: Number of explosions per iteration
explosions.name: Explosions

description: Defines the size of the that inner sting  \/
factor_inner_spike.name: Factor Inner Spike

description: The percent chance that this spell will fizzle
Fizzling means failing to cast while still consuming costs and incurring a cooldown
fizzle_chance.name: Fizzle Chance

description: Can be used to scale the text size down
font_size.name: Size

description: For upgrade items, this will force all properties in the upgrade template to apply to the target wand, even if they are a downgrade
force.name: Force

description: Whether or not the wand has uses
This is an internal property, you should not need to set it. It will be determined by the uses property being non-zero
has_uses.name: Has Uses

description: Set this to scale the amount of health healed linearly with the distance to the source
This can be used with an AreaOfEffect to heal targets more the closer they were to the cast target
Set this to the maximum distance, at which the heal amount will drop off to zero
heal_max_distance.name: Heal Max Distance

description: Amount of health to heal
health.name: Health

description: Height of an effect
height.name: Height

description: Height of the parabola arc forming the back
height_back.name: Height Back

description: Height per cell in blocks
height_cell.name: Height Cell

description: Make this wand a Heroes wand
If the Heroes plugin is installed, this wand will automatically fill its spell inventory with all of the Heroes skills the player has, and will display Heroes mana instead of Magic mana
heroes.name: Heroes

description: This spell or wand template will not show up in lists
This is generally used for templates not meant for player use
hidden.name: Hidden

description: How many entities the projectile can hit before expiring
hit_count.name: Hit Count

description: Which effects to play on hit
hit_effects.name: Hit Effects

description: If set to true, hit effects and actions will still execute on a miss
hit_on_miss.name: Hit On Miss

description: If set to true, hitting a block will count as a miss
hit_requires_entity.name: Hit Requires Entity

description: If true, hitbox targeting will be used
This will use the vanilla (or custom) hitboxes of target entities with projectile raycasts for line/box intersection tests
The exact hit location can be determined and used in effects, and special behavior can be given to headshots
hitbox.name: Hitbox

description: Can be used to expand a projectile's hitbox when determining block collisions
hitbox_block_size.name: Hitbox Block Size

description: Can be used to expand a projectile's hitbox when determining entity collisions
hitbox_size.name: Hitbox Size

description: The currently selected hotbar
Does not generally need to be set in a configuration
hotbar.name: Hotbar

description: The number of hotbars this wand has
Hotbars can be cycled using controls bound to the cycle_hotbar or cycle_hotbar_reverse actions
hotbar_count.name: Hotbar Count

description: Whether to play the hurt effect on the target, which will shake a player and turn their screen red
hurt.name: Hurt

description: Whether a falling block will damage entities it falls on
hurts.name: Hurts

description: The material to use when freezing water into ice
ice.name: Ice

description: An icon that represents a spell or wand
These can be vanilla items, or custom items from a resource pack
icon.name: Icon

description: An icon used when a spell is not available, due to permissions, cooldown, or insufficient resources
icon_disabled.name: Disabled Icon

description: A URL icon used when a spell is not available, due to permissions, cooldown, or insufficient resources
icon_disabled_url.name: Disabled Icon Url

description: If set, this wand will show a different icon when inactive versus when held, or for wands with a spell inventory, when the inventory is open
icon_inactive.name: Inactive Icon

description: An amount of time, in milliseconds, to wait before swapping the wand's active and inactive icons
icon_inactive_delay.name: Icon Inactive Delay

description: Set this to have the result of this action (and all sub-actions) ignored for the purposes of the overall spell result
This can be used to include some set of actions that are not deemed crucial to the success of the spell
It is commonly used on PlayEffects actions or BreakBlock actions when those are not the primary goal of the spell
This effects when a spell earns a cast for upgrade purposes and when it will earn SP
ignore_result.name: Ignore Result

description: Prevent this wand from despawning when dropped on the ground
immortal.name: Immortal

description: Increment the data value of blocks while iterating
This can be used with water or lava to taper the blocks off, lowering their height each iteration
increment_data.name: Increment Data

description: Sets the unbreakable tag on the wand item
This generally has to be set on a wand if using custom resource pack icons, to prevent the durability from changing
indestructible.name: Indestructible

description: A list of materials that can not be modified by this spell
indestructible_materials.name: Indestructible

description: Can be used to inherit from another template
inherit.name: Inherit

description: Whether to use reflect and break effects for instant (non-projectile) spells
instant_block_effects.name: Instant Block Effects

description: A spell to cast when a player interacts with (right-clicks on) this mob
interact_spell.name: Interact Spell

description: How often to update the projectile location
interval.name: Interval

description: How many rows to show in the spell inventory in chest and skills mobde
inventory_rows.name: Inventory Rows

description: Invert the text
invert.name: Invert

description: This wand will not take damage from any source, and can not be destroyed
invulnerable.name: Invulnerable

description: Whether or not this line zig zags
is_zig_zag.name: Is Zig Zag

description: The item to use or show
item.name: Item

description: Vanilla attributes to apply to this wand item
item_attributes.name: Item Attributes

description: Velocity to apply to dropped items
This generally nees to be set lower than velocity applied to living entities, or items will get thrown around too far
item_speed.name: Item Speed

description: The items to display
items.name: Items

description: Number of times to repeat the effect
iterations.name: Iterations

description: An amount of velocity to apply to this mount when the rider presses the jump key (space bar by default)
jump_controllable.name: Jump Controllable

description: If set, this wand will not be dropped on death
keep.name: Keep

description: If targeting a player, their wand will not be dropped on the ground but will be moved into their inventory
It will be put back on undo
keep_in_inventory.name: Keep In Inventory

description: What action the wand should perform when the player uses the swing (left-click by default) button
left_click.name: Left Click Binding

description: Where to play this effect
location.name: Location

description: The type of lock action to perform
lock_type.name: Lock Type

description: If set, this wand can not be modified
locked.name: Locked

description: The amount of mana this wand currently has
Can be used in a configuration to make a wand start out with mana, rather than waiting to regenerate
mana.name: Mana

description: The maximum amount of mana this wand can hold
mana_max.name: Mana Max

description: A percentage increase to give to a player's maximum mana when holding or wearing this wand
mana_max_boost.name: Mana Max Boost

description: How much mana should be recovered for each point of damage done by the holder
mana_per_damage.name: Mana Per Damage

description: Mana regeneration rate, in mana per second
mana_regeneration.name: Mana Regeneration

description: A percentage increase to give to a player's mana regeneration rate when holding or wearing this wand
mana_regeneration_boost.name: Mana Regeneration Boost

description: Where in player data should their marker location be saved
Can be used to have different spells track different marker locations
marker_key.name: Marker Key

description: The material to use
material.name: Material

description: The data value of the material being used
material_data.name: Material Data

description: A list of materials to use
materials.name: Materials

description: The maximum number of times this wand can be enchanted, using the legacy enchanting system
max_enchant_count.name: Max Enchant Count

description: How much health this mob should have
max_health.name: Max Health

description: Maximum amount of way points
max_way_points.name: Max Way Points

description: What type of message to send
message_type.name: Message Type

description: How often, in milliseconds, to cast a spell.
This parameter is deprecated, use 'interval' and triggers instead
mob_cast_interval.name: Cast Interval

description: How often to cast spells tied to the interval trigger
mob_interval.name: Interval

description: The display name of this mob
This is required for Magic Mobs
mob_name.name: Name

description: How this wand will present its spell inventory to the player
mode.name: Mode

description: The display name of this wand or spell to show in-game
Can be added directly on the wand or spell config, but it is often better to put all language in the messages.yml file so it can be easily edited and translated.
name.name: Name

description: Offset the original location
offset.name: Offset

description: Number of orbitals around the nucleus
orbitals.name: Orbitals

description: Parameters to apply to spells cast with this wand
Parameters can be global, or prefixed with a spell name such as 'blink.range 20' to apply only to a specific spell
Overrides can be manipulated in-game using the '/wand override' command
overrides.name: Overrides

description: The type of particle to use in this effect
particle.name: Particle

description: The type of particle to use for the first base of this effect
particle_base1.name: Particle Base1

description: The type of particle to use for the second base of this effect
particle_base2.name: Particle Base2

description: The number of particles to spawn with each particle packet
Use this with particle_offset_x,y,z to spawn a dense or sparse group of particles while sending only a single packet to the client
particle_count.name: Particle Count

description: The particle to use in the helix of this effect
particle_helix.name: Particle Helix

description: The particle to use in the nucleus of this effect
particle_nucleus.name: Particle Nucleus

description: A random spread of particles along the x-axis
Use with particle_count to spawn multiple particles per packet
particle_offset_x.name: Particle Offset X

description: A random spread of particles along the y-axis
Use with particle_count to spawn multiple particles per packet
particle_offset_y.name: Particle Offset Y

description: A random spread of particles along the z-axis
Use with particle_count to spawn multiple particles per packet
particle_offset_z.name: Particle Offset Z

description: The particle to use in the orbital of this effect
particle_orbital.name: Particle Orbital

description: A field to set in the contained effectlib effect, replacing a particle type with the casting particle type
Generally this comes from a wand, which are capable of having a custom particle type attached
For example, if set to 'particle', the 'particle' parameter of the contained effectlib effect will be automatically replaced with the particle set on the wand, if one is set.
particle_override.name: Particle Override

description: Radius of the rain/snow
particle_radius.name: Particle Radius

description: This can be used to give particles a set speed when spawned
The behavior varies between particle types
This will not work with colored particles
particle_speed.name: Particle Speed

description: The number of particles to spawn with each iteration of this effect
particles.name: Particles

description: The number of particles to spawn with each iteration of the inner effect
particles2.name: Particles2

description: Number of particles to be spawned in the helix per iteration
particles_helix.name: Particles Helix

description: Number of particles to be spawned in the nucleus per iteration
particles_nucleus.name: Particles Nucleus

description: Number of particles to be spawned in the orbital per iteration
particles_orbital.name: Particles Orbital

description: The amount of particles, displayed in one iteration
particles_per_iteration.name: Particles Per Iteration

description: If set, a wand will not activate when held
Instead, it will apply its affects when worn. Generally to be used with magic armor
passive.name: Passive

description: A progression path that a wand will follow
When enchanting or using the spellshop, a path will determine what spells are available to a player
Paths may upgrade to other paths in a progression, when a player learns all of the spells available on their current path they will progress to the next.
path.name: Path

description: How long to wait, in ticks, between each iteration
period.name: Period

description: Specify the pitch of the source direction
pitch.name: Pitch

description: An offset to apply to the pitch of the source direction
pitch_offset.name: Pitch Offset

description: If set, the holder of this wand will bypass many checks, allowing them to undo other player's spells, destroy normally indestructible blocks, and target normally untargable players.
Does not bypass the Super Protected setting
Requires the Magic.wand.use.powered permission to use
powered.name: Super Powered

description: If set, the holder of this wand will be completly invincible and untargetable by all spells
Magic.wand.use.protected permission to use
protected.name: Super Protected

description: Protection from specific damage types
protection.name: Protection

description: If set to true, this spell will not be castable at all in a pvp-restricted area

By default all spells will not target other players in pvp-restricted areas, but some spells like Fire can still be used to grief and so they are marked pvp_restricted: true to be unavailable in a no-pvp zone.
pvp_restricted.name: PVP Restricted

description: Radius of the nucleus as a fraction of the atom-radius
radius_nucleus.name: Radius Nucleus

description: How far, in blocks, this spell can reach before counting as a miss
This can apply to a base spell, which will do instant raycast targeting, or to a CustomProjectile which will travel over time until it reaches this distance
range.name: Range

description: Iterations to wait before refreshing particles
refresh.name: Refresh

description: Offset the source location based on the direction of that location
relative_offset.name: Relative Offset

description: Offset the source location based on the direction of that location
relative_source_offset.name: Relative Source Offset

description: Offset the target location based on the direction of that location
relative_target_offset.name: Relative Target Offset

description: A list of potion effects to remove from the target
remove_effects.name: Remove Effects

description: If true, this action will not run unless the spell has targeted an entity
Most spells that require entities will do this automatically, but occasionally you may with to turn off an entire branch of a spell because of there being no entity target.
requires_entity_target.name: Requires Entity Target

description: If true, this action will not run unless the spell has missed completely.
Missing usually means reaching max range or duration before hitting a solid block or entity
Most spells that require targets will do this automatically, but occasionally you may with to turn off an entire branch of a spell because of there being no target.
requires_target.name: Requires Target

description: What action the wand should perform when the player uses the interact (right-click by default) button
right_click.name: Right Click Binding

description: Rotation around the Y-axis
rotation.name: Rotation

description: Can be used to scale all costs for a shop up and down
scale.name: Scale

description: True to make this a sell shop, where players earn money by selling items
sell.name: Sell

description: The silent flag of the mob, to prevent it from making any sounds
silent.name: Silent

description: Size of the effect
size.name: Size

description: Angular movement per iteration
step.name: Step

description: Each stepX pixel will be shown. Saves packets for lower fontsizes.
step_x.name: Step X

description: Each stepY pixel will be shown. Saves packets for lower fontsizes.
step_y.name: Step Y

description: Number of steps to take per overall iteration
steps_per_iteration.name: Steps Per Iteration

description: If set to true, and this action returns a successful result, the spell will stop after this action has finished
Can be used to make some simple control flows in a spell
stop_on_success.name: Stop On Success

description: Gives damage bonuses to specific damage types
strength.name: Strength

description: What action the wand should perform when the player uses the swap (F by default) button
swap.name: Swap Binding

description: How this spell should perform its targeting
This only affects the initial targeting, not any projectiles that are launched
target.name: Targeting Mode

description: Set to true to allow this spell to target NPCs
target_npc.name: Target Npc

description: Offset the target location
target_offset.name: Target Offset

description: Whether or not this spell should targe the caster
This will affect projectiles, area of effect and other actions that target multiple entities
target_self.name: Target Self

description: A timeout in milliseconds, after which the projectile is allowed to target the caster
target_self_timeout.name: Target Self Timeout

description: Whether or not this spell is allowed to target tamed entities
target_tamed.name: Target Tamed

description: The class of entity this spell can target
This parameter does not use the normal EntityType enum, it refers directly to classes
This is so that it can be used with base classes like LivingEntity or Damageable to easily target a particular set of entity types
Use the target_types parameter if you instead want to target one or more EntityTypes specifically
target_type.name: Target Type

description: One or more specific entity types for this spell to target. The spell will ignore any entities not on this list
target_typs.name: Target Types

description: Whether this spell can be used on underwater targets
target_underwater.name: Target Underwater

description: Whether or not this spell may target unknown entities
This can be used to avoid targeting custom entities, which are generally pets from a pet plugin
target_unknown.name: Target Unknown

description: Whether or not this spell may target vanished players
target_vanished.name: Target Vanished

description: Offset the yaw of the target
target_yaw_offset.name: Target Yaw Offset

description: Used internally in item data to say which template a wand was created from
Do not set this in configurations
template.name: Template

description: Set this to allow a spell to be toggled on and off with subsequent casts.
Spells can either simply cancel when toggled off, or immediately perform their undo behaviors
toggle.name: Toggle

description: A value that will be used in lore
This is useful for spells that have a collection of repeat and delay actions, and so the total duration can not be automatically calculated
total_duration.name: Total Duration

description: A map of triggers that will cause this mob to cast spells
triggers.name: Triggers

description: The type of entity to spawn
type.name: Type

description: How long to wait, in milliseconds, before this spell will undo.
The timer starts when the spell finishes completely
undo.name: Undo

description: If set, only the onldest N changes will be undone
This can be used to create undo animations where blocks build while the tail end is undone
undo_oldest.name: Undo Oldest

description: If set, undo will happen over the course of several ticks
This is in terms of changes (blocks) per second
undo_speed.name: Undo Speed

description: If set, will trigger undo until the queue is has only N changes remaining
This can be used to create animations, such as in the Straem spell, where only the most recent few block changes are shown, and the rest are undone as the spell goes along.
undo_to.name: Undo To

description: If set, the wand will not be able to be dropped on the ground by the player
undroppable.name: Undroppable

description: If set, this wand will be given a unique id to prevent it from stacking
unique.name: Unique

description: Prevent the player from moving this wand in their inventory, it will be bound to a specific slot
unmoveable.name: Unmoveable

description: Allow teleporting to unsafe locations
unsafe.name: Unsafe

description: Prevent this wand from being put in a container
unstashable.name: Unstashable

description: If set to false, Entity-bound directions will not update during the Effect
update_directions.name: Update Directions

description: If set to false, Entity-bound locations will not update during the Effect
update_locations.name: Update Locations

description: How many times this spell must be successfully cast before it upgrades

Upgrades require that different spell levels have been defined. These levels have the same key as the base spell, but suffixed with a pipe (|) symbol and a level name. For instance, 'blink|2' is Blink level 2. Upgrade spells automatically inherit from the previous level, so each definition only needs to specify parameters that should change on upgrade.
upgrade_required_casts.name: Upgrade Required Casts

description: What path the player must be on before this spell can upgrade
This can be used to gate spell upgrades, preventing players from spam-casting to level all of their spells.

Upgrades require that different spell levels have been defined. These levels have the same key as the base spell, but suffixed with a pipe (|) symbol and a level name. For instance, 'blink|2' is Blink level 2. Upgrade spells automatically inherit from the previous level, so each definition only needs to specify parameters that should change on upgrade.
upgrade_required_path.name: Upgrade Required Path

description: Different options for the initial targeting of a spell.
target_type.name: Targeting Type

options.any: will target any entity, falling back to the player if no other entity was targeted
options.any_entity: will target any entity, falling back to the player if no other entity was targeted. Does not target blocks at all.
options.none: No target at all, can be used with some actions like Weather and Time
options.other: Will not target the caster, only other entities or blocks
options.other_entity: Will not target the caster, only other entities. Does not target blocks at all.
options.select: A special targeting mode for engineering spells, the first click will select a block and the second click will cast the spell using the selected block as the center or first target
options.select_entity: A special targeting mode, the first click will select and entity and the second click will cast the spell with that entity targeted. The entity may stay selected until the caster right-clicks.
options.self: Target the caster, often used with AreaOfEffect or buff spells
